\begin_layout Standard
In reality emphasizing 'she' as well as 'what' are both valid assignments
 of prominence.
 Having no emphasis in a sentence, by having monotonic speech would sound
 not natural and make the hearer wonder about the purpose of the utterance.
 However, when 'she' is emphasized, we assume that our focus is on her and
 the information coming next would probably involve additional details to
 support that fact.
 The same goes with 'what' only that this time we would expect details on
 what being said later on.
 
\end_layout

